Executive Profile
Leslie H. Cross  Chief Executive Officer and President, DJO, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Leslie H. Cross, also known as Les, serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President of DJO, LLC. Mr. Cross served as the Chairman of Alphatec Holdings, Inc. from July 2011 to December 10, 2016 and served as its Interim Chief Executive Officer from September 16, 2016 to December 10, 2016. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Alphatec Spine, Inc. Mr. Cross served as Chief Executive Officer of Alphatec Holdings, Inc. from February 28, 2012 to May 1, 2014. ... Mr. Cross served as the Chief Executive Officer of DJO Finance LLC (also known as DJOFL and ReAble Therapeutics Finance LLC) from November 2007 to June 1, 2011 and also served as its President from May 2008 to June 1, 2011. He served as the President of DJO Opco Holdings, Inc. from May 2008 to June 2011 and served as its Chief Executive Officer until June 2011. Mr. Cross served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Chattanooga Group, Inc. He served as Chief Executive Officer and President of DJO Opco Holdings, Inc., since August 2001. He served as the President of DJO Global, Inc. (formerly named DJO Incorporated and ReAble Therapeutics, Inc.) since May 2008. He served as principal executive roles at DJO Global and its predecessors since 1995. He served at Sonus Corporation. Mr. Cross served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of DJO Global, Inc. since August 2001. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Manager of DonJoy, L.L.C, the predecessor of DJO Incorporated, from June 1999 to November 2001 and served as President of DJ Orthopedics, LLC, a DJO Incorporated’s wholly-owned operating subsidiary, or its predecessor, the Bracing & Support Systems division of Smith & Nephew, Inc. (the “BASS Division”) since June 1995. From 1990 to 1994, Mr. Cross served as a Senior Vice President of Marketing and Business Development of the Bracing & Support Systems division of Smith & Nephew. He served as a Managing Director of two different divisions of Smith & Nephew, Inc. from 1982 to 1990. He worked at American Hospital Supply Corporation. He served as the Chairman of Alphatec Spine, Inc. since August 2011 until December 2016. He served as Chairman of DJO Opco Holdings, Inc., since June 2011 and its Director since August 2001. He served as the Chairman of DJO Global, Inc., from June 13, 2011 to December 31, 2011. He has been a Director of DTI Holdings, Inc. since May 17, 2012. He serves as a Director of BIOCOM, Inc. He served as a Director of Alphatec Spine, Inc. since March 29, 2011 until June 15, 2017. He served as a Director of Alphatec Holdings, Inc. since March 2011 until June 15, 2017. He served as a Director of DJO Global, Inc. (also known as DJO Incorporated) since August 2001. He served as a Director of DJO Finance LLC from November 2007 to December 4, 2012. Mr. Cross earned a diploma in Medical Technology from Sydney Technical College in Sydney, Australia and studied Business at the University of Cape Town in Cape Town, South Africa.Read Full Background




